    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-06T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-06T08:00:00-05:00" n="569"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d569">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5231/968: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-06T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >May 6, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 6—11:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. My telegrams 24, April 29, 1 p.m.; and 25, May 2, 5 p.m. For the quarter
                    ending June 30 French automobiles have been given a contingent equal to 10% of
                    automobiles imported same period last year. Informed orally by Foreign Office
                    this morning that American automobiles will receive 100% contingent. Same
                    percentage will be accorded British and German automobiles but Foreign Office
                    considers treatment accorded us very favorable since Spanish trade balance with
                    Germany equal and Spain has favorable trade balance with England and unfavorable
                    one with us.</p>
                <p>Foreign Office has intimated that it hopes for a great expedition in our treaty
                    negotiations and in view of the fact that preliminary Spanish-British commercial
                    negotiations now taking place and negotiations soon to begin with Brazil I
                    cannot overemphasize desirability of hastening our own negotiations now that
                    French and Spanish are virtually engaged in tariff war.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
